> The Steakhouse is a luxurious dinner night option, made with premium ingredients for a real taste of luxury at home!

== Cheesy Rosemary Fries ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide fries (no need to peel).

Pop the fries onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{1%tbsp}, season with @salt and @pepper, sprinkle over the @dried rosemary{1%tsp}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

== Burgers ==

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the garlic, @panko breadcrumbs{10%g}, half the @hard Italian style cheese{20%g}(grated), the @salt for breadcrumbs{1/4%tsp} and @water for breadcrumbs{2%tbsp}, then add the @British beef mince{240%g}.

Season with pepper and mix together with your hands.

Roll into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers onto a baking tray.

Bake on the middle shelf until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Steakhouse Style Peppercorn Sauce ==

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a medium #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the shallot and stir until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the @cracked black pepper{1%tsp} and stir in half the @cider vinegar{15%ml}. Allow the vinegar to bubble away.

Stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @water for sauce{100%ml} and allow it to reduce by about half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Reduce the heat, then stir in the @creme fraiche{75%g} and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

== Dressing and Assembly ==

In a medium bowl, mix the remaining @cider vinegar{15%ml} with the @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt and @pepper, mix well, then set aside.

When the fries have ~{5%minutes} left, remove from the oven and sprinkle over the remaining @hard Italian style cheese{20%g}(grated). Toss to coat, then return to the oven for the remaining time.

Meanwhile, halve the @burger buns{2} and pop them into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When you're ready to serve, toss the @baby leaf mix{50%g} through the dressing.

Top the bun bases with a small handful of salad, then a beef burger. Drizzle over some of your steakhouse style sauce, then sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Serve your craft burgers with your cheesy rosemary fries and the salad alongside. Pour the remaining sauce into a #pot{} for dipping. Enjoy!